Health Minister Zweli Mkhize has briefed the National Council of Provinces on the country's vaccine rollout strategy on Thursday. JOHANNESBURG - More than 32,000 health workers have been vaccinated against COVID-19. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize briefed the National Council of Provinces on the vaccine rollout. He says 500,000 doses of the vaccine will be received in the next few weeks. WATCH: COVID-19 Vaccine: SAA flight departs for Belgium The second phase of the vaccine rollout could take up to six months. The second phase will include frontline workers and people with comorbidities.